Efforts led to Air Force level outstanding unit awards 2012 and 2013. • Developed Air Force policy and special instructions for local strategies and base traffic plan; lectured senior management for operational decisions and created training for 13 thousand associate unit personnel. Recognized as best traffic safety program in Pacific region and reduced DUI rate on base 65%. • Project manager for construction of a commercial entry control facility; awarded $3.8 million from the Government of Japan for project development earned an "Excellent" rating during an Air Force required compliance inspection. • Organized joint international air show, two countries, 27 departments, 1000 event participants. Showcased more than $100 million in aircraft assets, viewed by more than 100 thousand U.S. and Japanese visitors. Flawless execution resulted in selection as senior manager of the quarter and Staff Manager of the year.

title: Anti-Terrorism senior analyst
description: • Senior advisor for all Force Protection/Physical Security and Anti-Terrorism initiatives for 14 bases; responsible for conducting Air Force compliance inspections and providing feedback to base leadership highlighting mitigation and cost analysis for courses of action. • Authored Integrated Defense Plan for forward operating base. 300 plus page plan that identified terrorist threats and provided mitigation plans for specific threat to the base. Provided a safe work environment for more than 200 personnel operating in a deployed location. • Developed the first travel advisory for Air Force personnel traveling to Mexico; provided guidance, threat data and travel restrictions, ensuring the safety of 41,000 personnel. • Motivational speaker for 12 operational courses and annual Commanders conference; motivation and speaking abilities lauded by Commander as “superior to peers”.

title: Assistant Operations Manager
description: • Led 41 person section executing 24-hour joint service force protection for 18K base residents and $32B in vital war fighting resources; awarded Law Enforcement Manager of the year. • Established local security plan for the President of The United States visit to Davis-Monthan AZ for three separate occasions. Coordinated with multiple local and federal agencies, ensured incident free event and solidified award for manager of the quarter. • Mentored 86 Afghanistan Military Officers; instructed mid level management skill sets and leadership techniques to equip foreign military personnel in the development and application personnel. Provided a stable security element enhancing the government of Afghanistan with 80% reduction in desertion. • Mentored 35 youth assigned to the Tucson Juvenile Detention Center promoting healthy development of troubled teens; provided youths with guidance, career and cultural enrichment opportunities, values and goals.
